Date: 14 July 2017 By: Anton van ZylViewed: 107The first match in the Limpopo Dairy League of the Louis Trichardt Cricket Club&nbsp;is scheduled for Sunday afternoon.The Limpopo Dairy team will face the Vikings. Vikings are the current &ldquo;champions&rdquo; of&nbsp;the previous T20 tournament.The league serves as a warm-up competition to prepare players for the new provincial season, which will start in September. In the Limpopo Dairy league, teams will battle it out over 18 overs, with each bowler limited to three overs.Five teams have entered for the competition and the rivalry is expected to be intense. Next Saturday (22nd) Vikings will play against Strikers. Strikers surprised friend and foe a few weeks ago by winning the six-a-side tournament.Cricket players who have not yet joined the club and are not playing for a team&nbsp;are invited to contact any of the committee members. The club treasurer, Ms Naomi Phillipson, can provide the necessary forms and information on membership fees. She can be contacted at 0824847622.Anton van Zyl has been with the Zoutpansberger and Limpopo Mirror for over 27&nbsp;years. He graduated at the the Rand Afrikaans University (now University of Johannesburg) and obtained a BA Communications degree. He is a founder member of the Association of Independent Publishers.Email: anton@zoutnet.co.zaMore photos... 